12.title: Deck Importing
12.body:
First you will need to create an account on swudb.com to make a deck. 

Or you can use sw-unlimited-db.com

Then once you've made a deck, you will have to copy the .json to your clipboard (at the bottom of the deck list page) and then paste that text into the text field of the importer object.

Then hit create deck and you're all good to go.

It's also important that you leave the deck of cards as they are for the importer to function properly.

function onObjectDrop(colorName, obj)
      scriptingZoneObjects1 = getObjectFromGUID("72ad23").getObjects()
      for i,v in ipairs(scriptingZoneObjects1) do
          if v == obj then
              if obj.type == "Tile" then

                  obj.destruct()
              elseif obj.type == "Dice" then
                  obj.destruct()
              end
              break
          end
      end

      scriptingZoneObjects2 = getObjectFromGUID("bc81b3").getObjects()
      for i,v in ipairs(scriptingZoneObjects2) do
          if v == obj then
              if obj.type == "Tile" then

                  obj.destruct()
              elseif obj.type == "Dice" then
                  obj.destruct()
              end
              break
          end
      end
end

function onObjectSpawn(obj)
  if obj.type == 'Card' then
      obj.addTag('Card')
  end
end

ObjectStates.Name: Custom_Token
ObjectStates.LuaScript:
--[[ Find the most recent version of this counter by going to https://steamcommunity.com/sharedfiles/filedetails/?id=2813676076
Customizable Counter by Jonathan Cox (aka JonGetsGames)

based on the Ludo Lodge Custom Counter Tokens by Ryan Langewisch which was
based on the excellent Universal Counter Tokens by MrStump

CUSTOMIZATION OPTIONS EXPLANATION

  Counter Type -  This has three important effects:
                  1. The type will be added to the counter's name so hovering will tell what type of thing is being counted.
                  2. The type will be used when printing value changes to the chat box.
                  3. IMPORTANT - Only counters with identical "type" will be able to transact with each other (explained below)

  Money Sybol - Only one character limit, if a symbol (like $) is placed here then this will be added to the counter
                value AND the "type" will no longer show in the chat box updates, instead this symbol is used.

  Show 'Type' on counter - displays the 'Type' name on the counter, underneath the value.

  Owner of this counter - This value is used for naming the counter when you hover over it as well as affecting
                          the text in the chat when the value changes.

  Print value changes to: - If "no players" then nothing is sent to chat. If "everyone" then the value change is sent to chat and
                            every player will see it. If "just you" then the value change is sent to chat and only you will see it.
                            If either "+ totals" option is selected, the phrase sent to chat will show the original and new values.

  Background color - Changes the background color of the counter.

  Value color - Changes the counter value number color.

  Shown adjustment buttons - Provides 4 options for which +/- buttons are shown on the counter.

  Transaction Options below - everything under this will only relate to how this counter transacts with other counters or the Supply

  Default transaction target - This shows a list of all counters that share this counter's "type", and always
                               also has "Infinite Supply" as an option. Infinite supply means the counter doesn't transact
                               with any other counter. If any other counter is selected, then this counter will default to spending
                               or sending it's value changes to that default counter.

  Show transaction buttons - When checked, this will show buttons under this counter for the Default Transaction Target as well as all
                             other counters that share this counter's "type". By pressing on those trasnaction buttons you change where
                             this counter transacts it's value changes to.

  Transactable with others - When this is checked, other counters with the same "type" will list this counter as a button. If you don't want
                             other counters to interact with this one, then uncheck the box.

  Infinite Supply Name - This is the name that shows up on the Infinite Supply transaction button, if "Infinite Supply" is set to default.

  Transaction Button Name - This is the name that will show up on transaction buttons on OTHER counters, that they can use to transact
                            with this counter. It's different from "Owner of this counter" because sometimes it's nice to have the transaction
                            button's name be shorthand to make the button smaller. Example: New York Central could have a button name of NYC.

  Number of buttons per row - This is the number of transaction buttons, including the Infinite Supply button if that's default, that will
                              show up under this counter when "Show transaction buttons" is checked.

  Width of each transaction button - Change this value to modify how wide every transaction button is.

  Height of each transaction button - Change this value to modify how tall every transaction button is.
]]

-- The following adjustment options are currently ONLY changable in this code, not in the Customization window.

-- Duration in seconds it waits until printing the value change to the chat box --
wait_duration = 1.25

-- Minimum and maximum values for this counter
MINIMUM_VALUE = -9999
MAXIMUM_VALUE = 9999

-- Background and text color for adjustment buttons and the "Customization toggle button --
ADJUSTMENT_BUTTON_BACKGROUND_COLOR = {1.0, 1.0, 1.0}
ADJUSTMENT_BUTTON_FONT_COLOR = {0, 0, 0}

-- Background and text color for the Infinite Supply transaction button, if it is set as the Default Transaction Target
bank_background_color = {1, 1, 1}           -- Button colors (RGB values from 0.0 to 1.0)
bank_font_color = {0, 0, 0}                 -- Button colors (RGB values from 0.0 to 1.0)

-- Value button parameters (this is what shows the current count)
VALUE_BUTTON_HEIGHT = 1
VALUE_BUTTON_WIDTH = 1
VALUE_BUTTON_HORIZONTAL_POSITION = 0     -- Negative for left, positive for right
VALUE_BUTTON_VERTICAL_POSITION_NO_TYPE = 0.08    -- Negative for up, positive for down
VALUE_BUTTON_VERTICAL_POSITION_WITH_TYPE = -0.2

-- Value button parameters (this is what shows the current count)
TYPE_BUTTON_HEIGHT = 1
TYPE_BUTTON_WIDTH = 1
TYPE_BUTTON_HORIZONTAL_POSITION = 0     -- Negative for left, positive for right
TYPE_BUTTON_VERTICAL_POSITION = 0.8    -- Negative for up, positive for down
TYPE_BUTTON_FONT_SIZE = 150

-- When "Money Symbol" is used (explained above in Customization explanation) this uses one digit.
ONE_DIGIT_FONT_SIZE = 500
TWO_DIGIT_FONT_SIZE = 500
THREE_DIGIT_FONT_SIZE = 480
FOUR_DIGIT_FONT_SIZE = 350
FIVE_DIGIT_FONT_SIZE = 275

-- +1 button parameters (button to add 1 to the count)
PLUS_ONE_BUTTON_FONT_SIZE = 300
PLUS_ONE_BUTTON_LABEL = '+1'

-- -1 button parameters (button to subtract 1 from the count)
MINUS_ONE_BUTTON_FONT_SIZE = 300
MINUS_ONE_BUTTON_LABEL = '-1'

-- +5 button parameters (button to add 5 to the count)
PLUS_FIVE_BUTTON_FONT_SIZE = 300
PLUS_FIVE_BUTTON_LABEL = '+5'

-- -5 button parameters (button to subtract 5 from the count)
MINUS_FIVE_BUTTON_FONT_SIZE = 300
MINUS_FIVE_BUTTON_LABEL = '-5'

-- +50 button parameters (button to add 5 to the count)
PLUS_FIFTY_BUTTON_FONT_SIZE = 250
PLUS_FIFTY_BUTTON_LABEL = '+50'

-- -50 button parameters (button to subtract 5 from the count)
MINUS_FIFTY_BUTTON_FONT_SIZE = 250
MINUS_FIFTY_BUTTON_LABEL = '-50'

-- This is the list used for the Customization backgrouna and font options.
-- Feel free to change the RGB values of any option to change how that color option looks.
color_options = {
  {color_name = "Black",   r=0.0,   g=0.0,     b=0.0},
  {color_name = "Blue",    r=0.118, g=0.53,    b=1.0},
  {color_name = "Brown",   r=0.443, g=0.231,   b=0.09},
  {color_name = "Green",   r=0.192, g=0.701,   b=0.168},
  {color_name = "Grey",    r=0.5,   g=0.5,     b=0.5},
  {color_name = "Orange",  r=0.956, g=0.392,   b=0.113},
  {color_name = "Pink",    r=0.96,  g=0.439,   b=0.807},
  {color_name = "Purple",  r=0.627, g=0.125,   b=0.941},
  {color_name = "Red",     r=0.856, g=0.0,     b=0.094},
  {color_name = "Teal",    r=0.129, g=0.694,   b=0.607},
  {color_name = "White",   r=1.0,   g=1.0,     b=1.0},
  {color_name = "Yellow",  r=0.905, g=0.898,   b=0.172}
}

--------------------------------------------
-- CHANGE CODE BELOW AT YOUR OWN RISK. :) --
--------------------------------------------

-- Transaction buttons parameters --
transact_BUTTON_VERTICAL_POSITION = 1.4        -- Negative for up, positive for down
transact_BUTTON_HEIGHT = 500
transact_BUTTON_WIDTH = 500
transact_BUTTON_FONT_SIZE = 200
transact_on_HEIGHT = 300

adjustment_button_options = {
  "None",
  "+/- 1",
  "+/- 1 and 5",
  "+/- 1, 5, and 50"
}
ledger_options = {
  "no players",
  "everyone",
  "everyone + totals",
  "just you",
  "just you + totals"
}

function onSpawn()
-- Activates when this counter is created, and pulls saved variable data to get everything matching.
  onSave()
  onLoad(saved_data)

  -- Opens up the customization panel so that a newly spawned counter can be easily customized
  Wait.time(function()
    updateValue()
    UpdateAfterCustomization()
    OpenCustomization()
  end, 0.1)


  Wait.time(function()

  end, 0.1)
end


function onLoad(saved_data)
-- Load save data and create buttons

  -- Initializing important variables
  transact_GUID = "Infinite Supply"
  default_transact_GUID = "Infinite Supply"
  printed = false
  ledger_option = "everyone"
  total_gained_count = 0
  click_count = 0
  button_count = 0
  customization_open = false
  buttons_per_row = 4
  fifty_buttons = true
  five_buttons = true
  any_transaction_buttons = true
  counter_controller = "Counter Name"
  counter_transact_button_name = "Name"
  infinite_supply_name = "Supply"
  money_symbol = " "
  any_adjustment_buttons = true
  VALUE_BUTTON_FONT_COLOR = {0, 0, 0}
  transactable = true
  --transact_with_others = false
  customization_explanations = false
  original_previous_value = nil
  show_type = false
  counter_name = self.getName()
  recursion_stopper_activated = false
  reset_hold = false


  -- Adds options to the right-click menu so that you can customize this counter, and use the description to set or modify the value.
  self.addContextMenuItem("Open Customization\n            Options", OpenCustomization)
  self.addContextMenuItem("Set Value to\n            Description", setCountFromDescription)
  self.addContextMenuItem("Modify Value\n            with Description", modifyCountFromDescription)


  -- Load saved count value if save data is found
  if saved_data != '' then
      local loaded_data = JSON.decode(saved_data)
      count = math.max(math.min(loaded_data.saved_count, MAXIMUM_VALUE), MINIMUM_VALUE)

      if loaded_data.saved_buttons_per_row ~= nil then
        buttons_per_row = loaded_data.saved_buttons_per_row
      end
      if loaded_data.saved_ledger_option ~= nil then
        ledger_option = loaded_data.saved_ledger_option
      end
      if loaded_data.saved_fifty_buttons ~= nil then
        fifty_buttons = loaded_data.saved_fifty_buttons
      end
      if loaded_data.saved_any_transaction_buttons ~= nil then
        any_transaction_buttons = loaded_data.saved_any_transaction_buttons
      end
      if loaded_data.saved_counter_controller ~= nil then
        counter_controller = loaded_data.saved_counter_controller
      end
      if loaded_data.saved_counter_transact_button_name ~= nil then
        counter_transact_button_name = loaded_data.saved_counter_transact_button_name
      end
      if loaded_data.saved_default_transaction_GUID ~= nil then
        default_transaction_GUID = loaded_data.saved_default_transaction_GUID
      end
      if loaded_data.saved_any_adjustment_buttons ~= nil then
        any_adjustment_buttons = loaded_data.saved_any_adjustment_buttons
      end
      if loaded_data.saved_five_buttons ~= nil then
        five_buttons = loaded_data.saved_five_buttons
      end
      if loaded_data.saved_infinite_supply_name ~= nil then
        infinite_supply_name = loaded_data.saved_infinite_supply_name
      end
      if loaded_data.saved_money_symbol ~= nil then
        money_symbol = loaded_data.saved_money_symbol
      end
      if loaded_data.saved_transactable ~= nil then
        transactable = loaded_data.saved_transactable
      end
      if loaded_data.saved_customization_explanations ~= nil then
        customization_explanations = loaded_data.saved_customization_explanations
      end
      if loaded_data.saved_VALUE_BUTTON_FONT_COLOR ~= nil then
        VALUE_BUTTON_FONT_COLOR = loaded_data.saved_VALUE_BUTTON_FONT_COLOR
      end
      if loaded_data.saved_transact_BUTTON_WIDTH ~= nil then
        transact_BUTTON_WIDTH = loaded_data.saved_transact_BUTTON_WIDTH
      end
      if loaded_data.saved_transact_BUTTON_HEIGHT ~= nil then
        transact_BUTTON_HEIGHT = loaded_data.saved_transact_BUTTON_HEIGHT
      end
      if loaded_data.saved_show_type ~= nil then
        show_type = loaded_data.saved_show_type
      end
      if loaded_data.saved_default_transact_GUID ~= nil then
        default_transact_GUID = loaded_data.saved_default_transact_GUID
      end
      if loaded_data.saved_transact_GUID ~= nil then
        transact_GUID = loaded_data.saved_transact_GUID
      end

    else
      count = MINIMUM_VALUE
    end

    UpdateCounterGUIDs()


    -- Populates the variables for button creation
    generateButtonParameters()
    -- Uses those variables to create all buttons
    createButtons()


    Wait.time(function()
      updateValue()
    end, 0.05)

    -- Puts a super quick time lag in to give time for the buttons to be made before letting other stuff activate once buttons are "created"
    if any_adjustment_buttons == true then
      Wait.time(function()
      buttons_created_already = true

      -- Activates the default (first) transaction button if transaction buttons are enabled.
      if any_transaction_buttons == true then
        ClickFunction1()
      end
    end,0.1)
    end
end


function onSave()
-- Save lots of important variables to save data
    local data_to_save = {saved_count = count,
                          saved_buttons_per_row = buttons_per_row,
                          saved_ledger_option = ledger_option,
                          saved_any_adjustment_buttons = any_adjustment_buttons,
                          saved_five_buttons = five_buttons,
                          saved_fifty_buttons = fifty_buttons,
                          saved_any_transaction_buttons = any_transaction_buttons,
                          saved_counter_controller = counter_controller,
                          saved_counter_transact_button_name = counter_transact_button_name,
                          saved_default_transaction_GUID = default_transaction_GUID,
                          saved_infinite_supply_name = infinite_supply_name,
                          saved_money_symbol = money_symbol,
                          saved_transactable = transactable,
                          saved_customization_explanations = customization_explanations,
                          saved_VALUE_BUTTON_FONT_COLOR = VALUE_BUTTON_FONT_COLOR,
                          saved_transact_BUTTON_WIDTH = transact_BUTTON_WIDTH,
                          saved_transact_BUTTON_HEIGHT = transact_BUTTON_HEIGHT,
                          saved_show_type = show_type,
                          saved_default_transact_GUID = default_transact_GUID,
                          saved_transact_GUID = transact_GUID
                          }
    saved_data = JSON.encode(data_to_save)
    return saved_data
end


function UpdateCounterGUIDs()
  -- Grabs all GUIDs for counters with the same "type" (set in customization menu) --
  -- Also counts the number of transaction buttons (including Infinite Supply if it's the default) --
  -- Also checks to see if any GUID matches this token, and removes that item from the list if it does --
  -- Also if any counter with a matching type is set to un-transactable (from customization menu) then it won't be added to the list --
  transact_BUTTONS_NUMBER = 0
  counter_GUIDs = {}

  table.insert(counter_GUIDs, default_transact_GUID)

  for _, object in ipairs(Global.getObjects()) do
    if object.getGMNotes() == self.getGMNotes() and object.getGUID() ~= self.getGUID() and object.getGUID() ~= default_transact_GUID then
      is_transactable = object.getVar("transactable")
      if is_transactable == true then
        if recursion_stopper_activated == false then
          Wait.time(function()
            object.setVar("recursion_stopper_activated", true)
            object.call("UpdateAfterCustomization")
            object.setVar("recursion_stopper_activated", false)
          end,0.1)
        end
        table.insert(counter_GUIDs, object.getGUID())
        transact_BUTTONS_NUMBER = transact_BUTTONS_NUMBER + 1
      end
    end
  end
end


function LedgerChange(gained_count, transact_name, current_click, previous_count)
-- Announces any value changes made on the counter, prints after a number of seconds (equal to wait_duration) have elapsed since the last button click
      -- figure out the number change and add to total transation for ledger --
      total_gained_count = total_gained_count + gained_count

      -- Defines the original value only the first time the button is pressed --
      if original_previous_value == nil then
        original_previous_value = previous_count
      end

      -- This only prints the ledger change once wait_duration number of seconds of no button presses have elapsed. --
      Wait.time(function()
        -- These will only equal if no more buttons have been pressed since the start of the Wait function --
        if current_click == click_count then
            -- This only prints if nothing has been printed already. Once it prints it sets to this to true and therefore only one ledger update happens even if multiple button presses happen to get there --
            if printed == false then
              string_to_print = ""
              if money_symbol == "" or money_symbol == " " then
                shown_pos_value = total_gained_count.." "..self.getGMNotes()
                shown_neg_value = (total_gained_count*-1).." "..self.getGMNotes()
              else
                shown_pos_value = money_symbol..total_gained_count
                shown_neg_value = money_symbol..(total_gained_count*-1)
              end

              if total_gained_count > 0 then
                string_to_print = " gained "..shown_pos_value
                if transact_GUID ~= "Infinite Supply" then
                  string_to_print = string_to_print.." from "..transact_name
                end
              elseif total_gained_count < 0 then
                string_to_print = " paid "..shown_neg_value
                if transact_GUID ~= "Infinite Supply" then
                  string_to_print = string_to_print.." to "..transact_name
                end
              end

              if string.sub(ledger_option, -6) == "totals" then
                string_to_print = string_to_print.." ("..original_previous_value.." -> "..count..")"
              end

              if total_gained_count ~= 0 then
                if string.sub(ledger_option, 1, 8) == "everyone" then
                  string_to_print = counter_controller..string_to_print
                  printToAll(string_to_print, self.getColorTint())
                elseif string.sub(ledger_option, 1, 8) == "just you" then
                  string_to_print = "You"..string_to_print
                  counter_color = TintToText()
                  printToColor(string_to_print, counter_color, "White")
                end
              end

              printed = true
            end
            -- Reset the overall ledger amount for the next set --
            total_gained_count = 0
            original_previous_value = nil
        end

      end,wait_duration)

      -- this sets it up to print the next ledger change on future button presses --
      printed = false

      --starts a timer that makes sure the transaction buttons won't be reset automatically too soon after a value change
      reset_hold = true
      Wait.time(function()
        reset_hold = false
      end,20)
end


-- Add 1 to the count, update the value button, and potentially print the change to the ledger
function add_one(print_ledger)
  previous_count = count
    -- This changes the count value and then updates the actual counter number on the token
    count = math.min(count + 1, MAXIMUM_VALUE)
    updateValue()

    -- If the player is transacting with a company, this adjusts that company value to show the amount removed or added
    if transact_GUID ~= "Infinite Supply" and print_ledger ~= "no_ledger" then
      counter = getObjectFromGUID(transact_GUID)
      counter.call("subtract_one","no_ledger")
    end

    -- This stops the ledger from updating if this function was activated by a different counter transacting with it
    if print_ledger ~= "no_ledger" then
      -- This is used to track if a button has been clicked for the purpose of waiting to print the ledger.
      click_count = click_count + 1
      LedgerChange(1, GetCounterDetails(transact_GUID).name, click_count, previous_count)
    end
end


-- Subtract 1 from the count, update the value button, and potentially print the change to the ledger
function subtract_one(print_ledger)
  previous_count = count
  -- This changes the count value and then updates the actual counter number on the token
    count = math.max(count - 1, MINIMUM_VALUE)
    updateValue()

    -- If the player is transacting with a company, this adjusts that company value to show the amount removed or added
    if transact_GUID ~= "Infinite Supply" and print_ledger ~= "no_ledger" then
      counter = getObjectFromGUID(transact_GUID)
      counter.call("add_one","no_ledger")
    end

    -- This stops the ledger from updating if this function was activated by a different counter transacting with it
    if print_ledger ~= "no_ledger" then
      -- This is used to track if a button has been clicked for the purpose of waiting to print the ledger.
      click_count = click_count + 1
      LedgerChange(-1, GetCounterDetails(transact_GUID).name, click_count, previous_count)
    end
end


-- Add 5 to the count, update the value button, and potentially print the change to the ledger
function add_five(print_ledger)
  previous_count = count

  -- This changes the count value and then updates the actual counter number on the token
    count = math.min(count + 5, MAXIMUM_VALUE)
    updateValue()

    -- If the player is transacting with a company, this adjusts that company value to show the amount removed or added
    if transact_GUID ~= "Infinite Supply" and print_ledger ~= "no_ledger" then

function ChangeTransactButtonColors(object, player_color, pressed_button_index, just_customized)
-- This updates the background color, font color, and height of each transaction button every time any transation button is pressed --
  -- If a button that has already been activated is clicked again, it reverts the transating target back to the bank --
  if transact_GUID == GetCounterDetails(counter_GUIDs[pressed_button_index]).GUID and just_customized == false then
    pressed_button_index = 1
  end
  -- This updates each transaction button based on their GUIDs in the array that created them.
  for button_index, GUID in ipairs(counter_GUIDs) do
    if button_index == pressed_button_index then
      -- This sets the pressed button to the active state, which makes the button's font color equal the company background, and the button's background equal the company font color.
      -- Also decreases the buttons height to make it more obvious which button is activated.
      self.editButton({index = button_index + 2, color = GetCounterDetails(GUID).font_color, font_color = GetCounterDetails(GUID).color})

      -- Same as above, but changes the big transaction display above the counter
      self.editButton({index = 2, label = "Transacting with\n"..GetCounterDetails(GUID).name, color = GetCounterDetails(GUID).color, font_color = GetCounterDetails(GUID).font_color})

      -- This sets transact_GUID to match the GUID of the currently transacting company, this variable is used elsewhere --
      transact_GUID = GetCounterDetails(GUID).GUID
    else

      -- This resets a button back to it's unselected state, based on the company token's backgrounad and font colors --
      self.editButton({index = button_index + 2, color = GetCounterDetails(GUID).color, font_color = GetCounterDetails(GUID).font_color, height = transact_BUTTON_HEIGHT})
    end
  end

  last_button_pressed_index = pressed_button_index

end


function setCountFromDescription(player_color)
-- Check if the description is a number, and set the count to that number
-- This is activated from a right-click context option.
    local new_value = self.getDescription()
    if new_value != '' and type(tonumber(new_value)) == 'number' then
      self.setDescription('')
      previous_count = count

      -- This changes the count value and then updates the actual counter number on the token
        count = math.min(new_value, MAXIMUM_VALUE)
        count_change = count - previous_count
        updateValue()

        -- If the player is transacting with a company, this adjusts that company value to show the amount removed or added
        if transact_GUID ~= "Infinite Supply" and print_ledger ~= "no_ledger" then
          counter = getObjectFromGUID(transact_GUID)
          other_counter_value = counter.getVar("count")
          counter.call("SetValueTo",other_counter_value - count_change)
        end

        -- This stops the ledger from updating if this function was activated by a different counter transacting with it
        if print_ledger ~= "no_ledger" then
          -- This is used to track if a button has been clicked for the purpose of waiting to print the ledger.
          click_count = click_count + 1
          LedgerChange(count_change, GetCounterDetails(transact_GUID).name, click_count, previous_count)
        end

    else
      printToColor("You must enter a number into the description box in order to change the counter's value.", player_color)
    end
end

function SetValueTo(value)
-- This is used if an outside script needs to change the value of the counter.
-- Do this by using this_counter_as_an_object_that_you_initialized.call("SetValueTo", newvalue)

  -- Actually change the value of the counter to the amount indicated.
  count = value
  updateValue()
end


function updateValue()
-- Update the value button according to the current count

  -- Changes the font size depending on how many digits there are, so that the value fits on the counter well.
  value_button_parameters.font_size = getValueButtonFontSize()

  -- If the Money Symbol customization is used, this adds that symbol to the front of the value shown.
  if money_symbol == "" or money_symbol == " " then
    value_button_parameters.label = tostring(count)
  else
    value_button_parameters.label = money_symbol .. tostring(count)
  end

  self.editButton(value_button_parameters)

  -- If someone changed the counter's name in the right-click field, this makes that name change real for the purposes of printing value changes.
  if self.getName() ~= counter_name then
    ChangeCounterName(player, self.getName(), id)
  end

  counter_name = self.getName()

end

function getValueButtonFontSize()
-- Return a font size based on the number of digits in the current count

  -- If Money Symbol customization is used, this adds 1 to the overall number of digits to account for it.
  local temp_count = count
  if money_symbol ~= "" and money_symbol ~= " " then
    temp_count = temp_count * 10
  end

  -- This checks the digit count and applies the correct variable size (that is set near the top of this code)
  if temp_count >= 0 and temp_count <= 9 then
      return ONE_DIGIT_FONT_SIZE
  elseif temp_count >= 10 and temp_count <= 99 then
      return TWO_DIGIT_FONT_SIZE
  elseif temp_count >= 100 and temp_count <= 999 then
      return THREE_DIGIT_FONT_SIZE
  elseif temp_count >=1000 and temp_count <= 9999 then
    return FOUR_DIGIT_FONT_SIZE
  elseif temp_count <= -1 and temp_count >= -9 then
      return TWO_DIGIT_FONT_SIZE
  elseif temp_count <= -10 and temp_count >= -99 then
      return THREE_DIGIT_FONT_SIZE
  elseif temp_count <= -100 and temp_count >= -999 then
      return FOUR_DIGIT_FONT_SIZE
  else
      return FIVE_DIGIT_FONT_SIZE
  end
end


function GetCounterDetails(GUID)
-- Returns a library with parameters about the counter associated with the passed GUID

  details = {GUID = GUID}

  -- If looking for details about a defaulted Infinite Supply then there is no token and therefore no GUID
  -- This sets the colors to the specified amount from variables at the top of this code for the bank.
  -- Otherwise, if it's not a bank then it returns information about the indicated company counter token.
  if GUID == "Infinite Supply" then
    details.name = "the ".. infinite_supply_name
    details.transaction_button_name = infinite_supply_name
    details.color = bank_background_color
    details.font_color = bank_font_color
  elseif GUID ~= nil then
    counter = getObjectFromGUID(GUID)
    details.name = counter.getVar("counter_controller")
    details.transaction_button_name = counter.getVar("counter_transact_button_name")
    details.color = counter.getColorTint()

    if buttons_created_already == true then
      -- This grabs all button info from the counter associated with the passed GUID
      buttons = counter.getButtons()

      -- This grabs the font color of the value of the counter, and this could be used for setting a transaction button font color if they are used.
      for index, info in ipairs(buttons) do
        if index == 1 then
          details.font_color = info.font_color
        end
      end
    end
  end

  return details
end

  generateButtonParameters()
  createButtons()

  Wait.time(function()
    updateValue()
  end, 0.05)

  -- This makes sure the "Customization" button stays in the "open" setting (since the button was just deleted and was remade with "closed" parameters)

    end, 0.05)
  end
]]

  -- As long as transaction buttons are enabled, this updates all the colors of them since they might have changed with customization.
  if any_transaction_buttons == true then

      ChangeTransactButtonColors(object, player_color, last_button_pressed_index, true)

function TransactResetTimer()
  Wait.time(function()
    if reset_hold == false then
      ChangeTransactButtonColors(object, player_color, 1, false)
    else
      TransactResetTimer()
    end
  end, 20)
end

-- Create buttons based on the button parameters
function createButtons()
    value_button_parameters.label = tostring(count)
    value_button_parameters.font_size = getValueButtonFontSize()

    -- This creates the big value number in the middle of the counter
    self.createButton(value_button_parameters)

    -- This creates the customization options button
    self.createButton(type_button_parameters)

    -- Everything within this If statement relates to having adjustment buttons on the counter.
    -- If this is set to "false" then the counter is only adjustable by outside means (specifically if this is a finite bank for other counters to interact with).
    if any_adjustment_buttons == true then
      -- Everything within this If statement relates to having the player counter transact with company counters.
      -- If this is set to "false" then this counter will not interact with any other counters of the same "type"
      if any_transaction_buttons == true then
        UpdateCounterGUIDs()

        -- This creates the "Transacting with" display button.
        self.createButton(transact_display_parameters)

        button_count = 1
        current_vertical_position = transact_BUTTON_VERTICAL_POSITION + (transact_BUTTON_HEIGHT * 0.00097)

        -- This cycles through every item in the counter_GUIDs table, that has GUIDs of all counters that have the same "type"
        for index, GUID in ipairs(counter_GUIDs) do

          -- This makes sure the number of buttons per row matches the value shown in Customization.
          -- It also makes sure the buttons are evenly spaced out depending on the height specified in Customization.
          if button_count > buttons_per_row then
            current_vertical_position = current_vertical_position + (transact_BUTTON_HEIGHT* 0.0021)
            button_count = 1
          end

          -- This creates a new function for the transaction button to then interact with when changing the transaction target.
          _G['ClickFunction' .. index] = function(object, player_color)
            ChangeTransactButtonColors(object, player_color, index, false)
            TransactResetTimer()
          end

          -- This figures out what the central position is considering the button's width and the number of buttons in the row.
          transact_BUTTONS_START_HORIZONTAL_POSITION = (buttons_per_row - 1) * (transact_BUTTON_WIDTH * 0.00105) * -1

          -- This bundles all the necessary information for the creation of the transaction button
          button_parameters = {
            click_function = 'ClickFunction' .. index,
            function_owner = self,
            label = GetCounterDetails(GUID).transaction_button_name,
            position = {  (transact_BUTTONS_START_HORIZONTAL_POSITION + (button_count - 1)*(transact_BUTTON_WIDTH * 0.0021)),
                           0.1,
                           current_vertical_position},
            width = transact_BUTTON_WIDTH,
            height = transact_BUTTON_HEIGHT,
            color = GetCounterDetails(GUID).color,
            font_color = GetCounterDetails(GUID).font_color,
            font_size = transact_BUTTON_FONT_SIZE,
            tooltip = "Transact with "..GetCounterDetails(GUID).name
          }
          self.createButton(button_parameters)
          button_count = button_count + 1
        end
      end

      -- Creates the +/- 1 adjustment buttons.
      self.createButton(plus_one_button_parameters)
      self.createButton(minus_one_button_parameters)

      -- Only creates +/- 5 adjustment buttons if specified by Customization.
      if five_buttons == true then
        self.createButton(plus_five_button_parameters)
        self.createButton(minus_five_button_parameters)
      end

      -- Only creates +/- 50 adjustment buttons if specified by Customization.
      if fifty_buttons == true then
        self.createButton(plus_fifty_button_parameters)
        self.createButton(minus_fifty_button_parameters)
      end
    end
end


function generateButtonParameters()
-- Load button parameters into tables for button creation

  -- Change adjustment button parameters depending on which adjustment button set is indicated by Customization.
  if fifty_buttons == true then
    adjust_button_height = 400
    adjust_button_width = 550
    plus_horizontal_position = 2.1
    minus_horizontal_position = -2.1
    row1_vertical_position = -0.8
    row2_vertical_position = 0
    row3_vertical_position = 0.8
  elseif five_buttons == true then
    adjust_button_height = 500
    adjust_button_width = 500
    plus_horizontal_position = 2.1
    minus_horizontal_position = -2.1
    row1_vertical_position = -0.6
    row2_vertical_position = 0.6
  else
    adjust_button_height = 1100
    adjust_button_width = 500
    plus_horizontal_position = 2.1
    minus_horizontal_position = -2.1
    row1_vertical_position = 0
    row2_vertical_position = 0.6

  if show_type == false then
    VALUE_BUTTON_VERTICAL_POSITION = VALUE_BUTTON_VERTICAL_POSITION_NO_TYPE
    shown_type_label = ""
  else
    VALUE_BUTTON_VERTICAL_POSITION = VALUE_BUTTON_VERTICAL_POSITION_WITH_TYPE
    shown_type_label = self.getGMNotes()
  end

  -- Creates bundled paramater variables for the creation of buttons.
  value_button_parameters = {
      index = 0, click_function = 'NotARealFunction', function_owner = self, label = '',
      position = {VALUE_BUTTON_HORIZONTAL_POSITION, 0.1, VALUE_BUTTON_VERTICAL_POSITION},
      width = VALUE_BUTTON_WIDTH, height = VALUE_BUTTON_HEIGHT,
      color = ADJUSTMENT_BUTTON_BACKGROUND_COLOR, font_color = VALUE_BUTTON_FONT_COLOR,
      scale = {x=2,y=2,z=2},
      font_size = getValueButtonFontSize()
  }
  type_button_parameters = {
      click_function = 'NotARealFunction', function_owner = self, label = shown_type_label,
      position = {TYPE_BUTTON_HORIZONTAL_POSITION, 0.1, TYPE_BUTTON_VERTICAL_POSITION},
      width = TYPE_BUTTON_WIDTH, height = TYPE_BUTTON_HEIGHT,
      color = ADJUSTMENT_BUTTON_BACKGROUND_COLOR, font_color = VALUE_BUTTON_FONT_COLOR,
      scale = {x=2,y=2,z=2},
      font_size = TYPE_BUTTON_FONT_SIZE
  }
  plus_one_button_parameters = {
      click_function = 'add_one', function_owner = self, label = PLUS_ONE_BUTTON_LABEL,
      position = {plus_horizontal_position, 0.1, row1_vertical_position},
      width = adjust_button_width, height = adjust_button_height,
      color = ADJUSTMENT_BUTTON_BACKGROUND_COLOR, font_color = ADJUSTMENT_BUTTON_FONT_COLOR,
      font_size = PLUS_ONE_BUTTON_FONT_SIZE
  }
  minus_one_button_parameters = {
      click_function = 'subtract_one', function_owner = self, label = MINUS_ONE_BUTTON_LABEL,
      position = {minus_horizontal_position, 0.1, row1_vertical_position},
      width = adjust_button_width, height = adjust_button_height,
      color = ADJUSTMENT_BUTTON_BACKGROUND_COLOR, font_color = ADJUSTMENT_BUTTON_FONT_COLOR,
      font_size = MINUS_ONE_BUTTON_FONT_SIZE
  }
  plus_five_button_parameters = {
      click_function = 'add_five', function_owner = self, label = PLUS_FIVE_BUTTON_LABEL,
      position = {plus_horizontal_position, 0.1, row2_vertical_position},
      width = adjust_button_width, height = adjust_button_height,
      color = ADJUSTMENT_BUTTON_BACKGROUND_COLOR, font_color = ADJUSTMENT_BUTTON_FONT_COLOR,
      font_size = PLUS_FIVE_BUTTON_FONT_SIZE

function OpenCustomization(player, value, id)
-- Function to open the customization XML window

    -- This recreates the list of counters that share a type because new counters might have been made, or had types changed to match.
      UpdateCounterGUIDs()

    -- This changes the XML values to match the current values for all these customization attributes.
    self.UI.setAttribute("NumberOfRows", "text", buttons_per_row)
    self.UI.setAttribute("TransactionButtonWidth","text", transact_BUTTON_WIDTH)
    self.UI.setAttribute("TransactionButtonHeight","text", transact_BUTTON_HEIGHT)
    self.UI.setAttribute("FiftiesToggle", "isOn",fifty_buttons)
    self.UI.setAttribute("CounterType", "text", self.getGMNotes())
    self.UI.setAttribute("CounterName", "text", counter_controller)
    self.UI.setAttribute("CounterTransactButtonName", "text", counter_transact_button_name)
    self.UI.setAttribute("TransactionButtonsToggle", "isOn",any_transaction_buttons)
    self.UI.setAttribute("InfiniteSupplyName", "text", infinite_supply_name)
    self.UI.setAttribute("MoneySymbol", "text", money_symbol)
    self.UI.setAttribute("TransactableToggle", "isOn", transactable)
    self.UI.setAttribute("ShowTypeToggle", "isOn", show_type)
    --self.UI.setAttribute("TransactionsToggle", "isOn", transact_with_others)



    -- This grabs all XML data and puts it into a table.
    local xml = self.UI.getXmlTable()

    -- This builds the dropdown options for which ledger options are used and modifies the XML data table accordingly.
    xml[2].children[8].children[5].children[2].children[1].children = {}

    for _, value in ipairs(ledger_options) do
      if value == ledger_option then
        is_selected = true
      else
        is_selected = false
      end
      add_adjustment_buttons_option = {
          tag="Option",
          value = value,
          attributes={selected = is_selected},
          children={}
      }
      table.insert(xml[2].children[8].children[5].children[2].children[1].children, add_adjustment_buttons_option)
    end

    -- This builds the dropdown options for changing the background color and modifies the XML data table accordingly.
    xml[2].children[8].children[6].children[2].children[1].children = {}
    for _, color in ipairs(color_options) do
      if trunc(self.getColorTint().r,1) == trunc(color.r,1) and trunc(self.getColorTint().g,1) == trunc(color.g,1) and trunc(self.getColorTint().b,1) == trunc(color.b,1) then
        is_selected = true
      else
        is_selected = false
      end
      add_BGcolor_option = {
          tag="Option",
          value = color.color_name,
          attributes={selected = is_selected},
          children={}
      }
      table.insert(xml[2].children[8].children[6].children[2].children[1].children, add_BGcolor_option)
    end

    -- This builds the dropdown options for changing the shown value color and modifies the XML data table accordingly.
    xml[2].children[8].children[7].children[2].children[1].children = {}
    for _, color in ipairs(color_options) do
      if trunc(VALUE_BUTTON_FONT_COLOR[1],1) == trunc(color.r,1) and trunc(VALUE_BUTTON_FONT_COLOR[2],1) == trunc(color.g,1) and trunc(VALUE_BUTTON_FONT_COLOR[3],1) == trunc(color.b,1) then
        is_selected = true
      else
        is_selected = false
      end
      add_value_color_option = {
          tag="Option",
          value = color.color_name,
          attributes={selected = is_selected},
          children={}
      }
      table.insert(xml[2].children[8].children[7].children[2].children[1].children, add_value_color_option)
    end


    -- This builds the dropdown options for which adjustment buttons are shown and modifies the XML data table accordingly.
    xml[2].children[8].children[8].children[2].children[1].children = {}
    if any_adjustment_buttons == false then
      current_shown_adjustment_buttons = "e"
    elseif five_buttons == false then
      current_shown_adjustment_buttons = "1"
    elseif five_buttons == true and fifty_buttons == false then
      current_shown_adjustment_buttons = "5"
    elseif fifty_buttons == true then
      current_shown_adjustment_buttons = "0"
    end

    for _, value in ipairs(adjustment_button_options) do
      if string.sub(value, -1) == current_shown_adjustment_buttons then
        is_selected = true
      else
        is_selected = false
      end
      add_adjustment_buttons_option = {
          tag="Option",
          value = value,
          attributes={selected = is_selected},
          children={}
      }
      table.insert(xml[2].children[8].children[8].children[2].children[1].children, add_adjustment_buttons_option)
    end

    UpdateCounterGUIDs()

    -- This builds the dropdown options for all the counters that can be set to the default transaction target and modifies the XML data table accordingly.
    add_default_option ={ tag="Option",
                  value = "Infinite Supply",
                  attributes={},
                  children={}
    }
    xml[2].children[8].children[10].children[2].children[1].children = {add_default_option}
    log(default_transact_GUID)
    for _, GUID in ipairs(counter_GUIDs) do
      if GUID ~= "Infinite Supply" then
        if default_transact_GUID == GUID then
          is_selected = true
        else
          is_selected = false
        end
        add_default_option = {
            tag="Option",
            value = GetCounterDetails(GUID).transaction_button_name ..": ".. GetCounterDetails(GUID).GUID,
            attributes={selected = is_selected},
            children={}
        }
        table.insert(xml[2].children[8].children[10].children[2].children[1].children, add_default_option)
      end
    end

    -- Replaces this counter's XML data with the modified data from the XML table that was created.
    self.UI.setXmlTable(xml)

    -- This un-hides the Customization XML window so that it's visible and able to be used.
    self.UI.show("Customization_Window")

    -- Changes the "Customization" button's colors to show that it's currently in use.
--    self.editButton({index=1, color=ADJUSTMENT_BUTTON_FONT_COLOR, font_color=ADJUSTMENT_BUTTON_BACKGROUND_COLOR})

    customization_open = true
end


function CloseCustomization(player, value, id)
-- This closes (hides) the Customization XML window.
    UpdateCounterGUIDs()

    self.UI.hide("Customization_Window")

    self.UI.hide("Customization_Explanations")
    customization_explanations = false

    customization_open = false
    UpdateAfterCustomization()

    -- Changes the "Customization" button's colors to show that it's no longer in use.
--    self.editButton({index=1, color=ADJUSTMENT_BUTTON_BACKGROUND_COLOR, font_color=ADJUSTMENT_BUTTON_FONT_COLOR})
end


function ToggleCustomizationExplanations()
-- This opens and closes the "help" panel which explains all the customization options --
  if customization_explanations == true then
    self.UI.hide("Customization_Explanations")
    customization_explanations = false
  else
    self.UI.show("Customization_Explanations")
    customization_explanations = true
  end
end

function TintToText()
  for _, color in ipairs(color_options) do
    if trunc(self.getColorTint().r,1) == trunc(color.r,1) and trunc(self.getColorTint().g,1) == trunc(color.g,1) and trunc(self.getColorTint().b,1) == trunc(color.b,1) then
      bg_color = color.color_name
    end
  end

  return bg_color
end

-- This exists so that the code doesn't have an error. leave it and ignore it.
function NotARealFunction()
end

-- This is a nice little function I found somewhere online that makes truncating a value simple to do.
function trunc(num, digits)
  local mult = 10^(digits)
  return math.modf(num*mult)/mult
end

-- This is an awesome little function I found online that "dumps" all information from a table into the chat box
-- and is entirely used for debugging and discovery. I kept it here because I may need it for future development on this counter.
function dump(o)
   if type(o) == 'table' then
      local s = '{ '
      for k,v in pairs(o) do
         if type(k) ~= 'number' then k = '"'..k..'"' end
         s = s .. '['..k..'] = ' .. dump(v) .. ','
      end
      return s .. '} \n'
   else
      return tostring(o)
   end
end

--[[ Find the most recent version of this counter by going to https://steamcommunity.com/sharedfiles/filedetails/?id=2813676076
Customizable Counter by Jonathan Cox (aka JonGetsGames)

based on the Ludo Lodge Custom Counter Tokens by Ryan Langewisch which was
based on the excellent Universal Counter Tokens by MrStump

CUSTOMIZATION OPTIONS EXPLANATION

  Counter Type -  This has three important effects:
                  1. The type will be added to the counter's name so hovering will tell what type of thing is being counted.
                  2. The type will be used when printing value changes to the chat box.
                  3. IMPORTANT - Only counters with identical "type" will be able to transact with each other (explained below)

  Money Sybol - Only one character limit, if a symbol (like $) is placed here then this will be added to the counter
                value AND the "type" will no longer show in the chat box updates, instead this symbol is used.

  Show 'Type' on counter - displays the 'Type' name on the counter, underneath the value.

  Owner of this counter - This value is used for naming the counter when you hover over it as well as affecting
                          the text in the chat when the value changes.

  Print value changes to: - If "no players" then nothing is sent to chat. If "everyone" then the value change is sent to chat and
                            every player will see it. If "just you" then the value change is sent to chat and only you will see it.
                            If either "+ totals" option is selected, the phrase sent to chat will show the original and new values.

  Background color - Changes the background color of the counter.

  Value color - Changes the counter value number color.

  Shown adjustment buttons - Provides 4 options for which +/- buttons are shown on the counter.

  Transaction Options below - everything under this will only relate to how this counter transacts with other counters or the Supply

  Default transaction target - This shows a list of all counters that share this counter's "type", and always
                               also has "Infinite Supply" as an option. Infinite supply means the counter doesn't transact
                               with any other counter. If any other counter is selected, then this counter will default to spending
                               or sending it's value changes to that default counter.

  Show transaction buttons - When checked, this will show buttons under this counter for the Default Transaction Target as well as all
                             other counters that share this counter's "type". By pressing on those trasnaction buttons you change where
                             this counter transacts it's value changes to.

  Transactable with others - When this is checked, other counters with the same "type" will list this counter as a button. If you don't want
                             other counters to interact with this one, then uncheck the box.

  Infinite Supply Name - This is the name that shows up on the Infinite Supply transaction button, if "Infinite Supply" is set to default.

  Transaction Button Name - This is the name that will show up on transaction buttons on OTHER counters, that they can use to transact
                            with this counter. It's different from "Owner of this counter" because sometimes it's nice to have the transaction
                            button's name be shorthand to make the button smaller. Example: New York Central could have a button name of NYC.

  Number of buttons per row - This is the number of transaction buttons, including the Infinite Supply button if that's default, that will
                              show up under this counter when "Show transaction buttons" is checked.

  Width of each transaction button - Change this value to modify how wide every transaction button is.

  Height of each transaction button - Change this value to modify how tall every transaction button is.
]]

function onSpawn()

  onSave()
  onLoad(saved_data)

  Wait.time(function()
    updateValue()
    UpdateAfterCustomization()
    OpenCustomization()
  end, 0.1)


  Wait.time(function()

end


function onLoad(saved_data)

  transact_GUID = "Infinite Supply"
  default_transact_GUID = "Infinite Supply"
  printed = false
  ledger_option = "everyone"
  total_gained_count = 0
  click_count = 0
  button_count = 0
  customization_open = false

  fifty_buttons = true
  five_buttons = true
  any_transaction_buttons = true

  counter_transact_button_name = "Name"

  money_symbol = " "
  any_adjustment_buttons = true

  customization_explanations = false
  original_previous_value = nil
  show_type = false
  counter_name = self.getName()
  recursion_stopper_activated = false
  reset_hold = false


  -- Adds options to the right-click menu so that you can customize this counter, and use the description to set or modify the value.
  self.addContextMenuItem("Open Customization\n            Options", OpenCustomization)
  self.addContextMenuItem("Set Value to\n            Description", setCountFromDescription)
  self.addContextMenuItem("Modify Value\n            with Description", modifyCountFromDescription)

  if saved_data != '' then

      end

                          saved_transact_GUID = transact_GUID
                          }
    saved_data = JSON.encode(data_to_save)
    return saved_data
end


function UpdateCounterGUIDs()
  -- Grabs all GUIDs for counters with the same "type" (set in customization menu) --
  -- Also counts the number of transaction buttons (including Infinite Supply if it's the default) --
  -- Also checks to see if any GUID matches this token, and removes that item from the list if it does --
  -- Also if any counter with a matching type is set to un-transactable (from customization menu) then it won't be added to the list --
  transact_BUTTONS_NUMBER = 0
  counter_GUIDs = {}

  table.insert(counter_GUIDs, default_transact_GUID)

  for _, object in ipairs(Global.getObjects()) do
    if object.getGMNotes() == self.getGMNotes() and object.getGUID() ~= self.getGUID() and object.getGUID() ~= default_transact_GUID then
      is_transactable = object.getVar("transactable")
      if is_transactable == true then
        if recursion_stopper_activated == false then
          Wait.time(function()
            object.setVar("recursion_stopper_activated", true)
            object.call("UpdateAfterCustomization")
            object.setVar("recursion_stopper_activated", false)
          end,0.1)
        end
        table.insert(counter_GUIDs, object.getGUID())
        transact_BUTTONS_NUMBER = transact_BUTTONS_NUMBER + 1
      end
    end
  end
end


function LedgerChange(gained_count, transact_name, current_click, previous_count)
-- Announces any value changes made on the counter, prints after a number of seconds (equal to wait_duration) have elapsed since the last button click
      -- figure out the number change and add to total transation for ledger --
      total_gained_count = total_gained_count + gained_count

      -- Defines the original value only the first time the button is pressed --
      if original_previous_value == nil then
        original_previous_value = previous_count
      end

      -- This only prints the ledger change once wait_duration number of seconds of no button presses have elapsed. --
      Wait.time(function()
        -- These will only equal if no more buttons have been pressed since the start of the Wait function --
        if current_click == click_count then
            -- This only prints if nothing has been printed already. Once it prints it sets to this to true and therefore only one ledger update happens even if multiple button presses happen to get there --
            if printed == false then
              string_to_print = ""
              if money_symbol == "" or money_symbol == " " then
                shown_pos_value = total_gained_count.." "..self.getGMNotes()
                shown_neg_value = (total_gained_count*-1).." "..self.getGMNotes()
              else
                shown_pos_value = money_symbol..total_gained_count
                shown_neg_value = money_symbol..(total_gained_count*-1)
              end

              if total_gained_count > 0 then
                string_to_print = " gained "..shown_pos_value
                if transact_GUID ~= "Infinite Supply" then
                  string_to_print = string_to_print.." from "..transact_name
                end
              elseif total_gained_count < 0 then
                string_to_print = " paid "..shown_neg_value
                if transact_GUID ~= "Infinite Supply" then
                  string_to_print = string_to_print.." to "..transact_name
                end
              end

              if string.sub(ledger_option, -6) == "totals" then
                string_to_print = string_to_print.." ("..original_previous_value.." -> "..count..")"
              end

              if total_gained_count ~= 0 then
                if string.sub(ledger_option, 1, 8) == "everyone" then
                  string_to_print = counter_controller..string_to_print
                  printToAll(string_to_print, self.getColorTint())
                elseif string.sub(ledger_option, 1, 8) == "just you" then
                  string_to_print = "You"..string_to_print
                  counter_color = TintToText()
                  printToColor(string_to_print, counter_color, "White")
                end
              end

              printed = true
            end
            -- Reset the overall ledger amount for the next set --
            total_gained_count = 0
            original_previous_value = nil
        end

      end,wait_duration)

      -- this sets it up to print the next ledger change on future button presses --
      printed = false

      --starts a timer that makes sure the transaction buttons won't be reset automatically too soon after a value change
      reset_hold = true
      Wait.time(function()
        reset_hold = false
      end,20)
end


-- Add 1 to the count, update the value button, and potentially print the change to the ledger
function add_one(print_ledger)
  previous_count = count
    -- This changes the count value and then updates the actual counter number on the token
    count = math.min(count + 1, MAXIMUM_VALUE)
    updateValue()

    -- If the player is transacting with a company, this adjusts that company value to show the amount removed or added
    if transact_GUID ~= "Infinite Supply" and print_ledger ~= "no_ledger" then
      counter = getObjectFromGUID(transact_GUID)
      counter.call("subtract_one","no_ledger")
    end

    -- This stops the ledger from updating if this function was activated by a different counter transacting with it
    if print_ledger ~= "no_ledger" then
      -- This is used to track if a button has been clicked for the purpose of waiting to print the ledger.
      click_count = click_count + 1
      LedgerChange(1, GetCounterDetails(transact_GUID).name, click_count, previous_count)
    end
end

function ChangeTransactButtonColors(object, player_color, pressed_button_index, just_customized)
-- This updates the background color, font color, and height of each transaction button every time any transation button is pressed --
  -- If a button that has already been activated is clicked again, it reverts the transating target back to the bank --
  if transact_GUID == GetCounterDetails(counter_GUIDs[pressed_button_index]).GUID and just_customized == false then
    pressed_button_index = 1
  end
  -- This updates each transaction button based on their GUIDs in the array that created them.
  for button_index, GUID in ipairs(counter_GUIDs) do
    if button_index == pressed_button_index then
      -- This sets the pressed button to the active state, which makes the button's font color equal the company background, and the button's background equal the company font color.
      -- Also decreases the buttons height to make it more obvious which button is activated.
      self.editButton({index = button_index + 2, color = GetCounterDetails(GUID).font_color, font_color = GetCounterDetails(GUID).color})

      -- Same as above, but changes the big transaction display above the counter
      self.editButton({index = 2, label = "Transacting with\n"..GetCounterDetails(GUID).name, color = GetCounterDetails(GUID).color, font_color = GetCounterDetails(GUID).font_color})

      -- This sets transact_GUID to match the GUID of the currently transacting company, this variable is used elsewhere --
      transact_GUID = GetCounterDetails(GUID).GUID
    else

      -- This resets a button back to it's unselected state, based on the company token's backgrounad and font colors --
      self.editButton({index = button_index + 2, color = GetCounterDetails(GUID).color, font_color = GetCounterDetails(GUID).font_color, height = transact_BUTTON_HEIGHT})
    end
  end

  last_button_pressed_index = pressed_button_index

end


function setCountFromDescription(player_color)
-- Check if the description is a number, and set the count to that number
-- This is activated from a right-click context option.
    local new_value = self.getDescription()
    if new_value != '' and type(tonumber(new_value)) == 'number' then
      self.setDescription('')
      previous_count = count

      -- This changes the count value and then updates the actual counter number on the token
        count = math.min(new_value, MAXIMUM_VALUE)
        count_change = count - previous_count
        updateValue()

        -- If the player is transacting with a company, this adjusts that company value to show the amount removed or added
        if transact_GUID ~= "Infinite Supply" and print_ledger ~= "no_ledger" then
          counter = getObjectFromGUID(transact_GUID)
          other_counter_value = counter.getVar("count")
          counter.call("SetValueTo",other_counter_value - count_change)
        end

        -- This stops the ledger from updating if this function was activated by a different counter transacting with it
        if print_ledger ~= "no_ledger" then
          -- This is used to track if a button has been clicked for the purpose of waiting to print the ledger.
          click_count = click_count + 1
          LedgerChange(count_change, GetCounterDetails(transact_GUID).name, click_count, previous_count)
        end

    else
      printToColor("You must enter a number into the description box in order to change the counter's value.", player_color)
    end
end

function SetValueTo(value)
-- This is used if an outside script needs to change the value of the counter.
-- Do this by using this_counter_as_an_object_that_you_initialized.call("SetValueTo", newvalue)

  -- Actually change the value of the counter to the amount indicated.
  count = value
  updateValue()
end


function updateValue()
-- Update the value button according to the current count

  -- Changes the font size depending on how many digits there are, so that the value fits on the counter well.
  value_button_parameters.font_size = getValueButtonFontSize()

  -- If the Money Symbol customization is used, this adds that symbol to the front of the value shown.
  if money_symbol == "" or money_symbol == " " then
    value_button_parameters.label = tostring(count)
  else
    value_button_parameters.label = money_symbol .. tostring(count)
  end

  self.editButton(value_button_parameters)

  -- If someone changed the counter's name in the right-click field, this makes that name change real for the purposes of printing value changes.
  if self.getName() ~= counter_name then
    ChangeCounterName(player, self.getName(), id)
  end

  counter_name = self.getName()

end

function getValueButtonFontSize()
-- Return a font size based on the number of digits in the current count

  -- If Money Symbol customization is used, this adds 1 to the overall number of digits to account for it.
  local temp_count = count
  if money_symbol ~= "" and money_symbol ~= " " then
    temp_count = temp_count * 10
  end

  -- This checks the digit count and applies the correct variable size (that is set near the top of this code)
  if temp_count >= 0 and temp_count <= 9 then
      return ONE_DIGIT_FONT_SIZE
  elseif temp_count >= 10 and temp_count <= 99 then
      return TWO_DIGIT_FONT_SIZE
  elseif temp_count >= 100 and temp_count <= 999 then
      return THREE_DIGIT_FONT_SIZE
  elseif temp_count >=1000 and temp_count <= 9999 then
    return FOUR_DIGIT_FONT_SIZE
  elseif temp_count <= -1 and temp_count >= -9 then
      return TWO_DIGIT_FONT_SIZE
  elseif temp_count <= -10 and temp_count >= -99 then
      return THREE_DIGIT_FONT_SIZE
  elseif temp_count <= -100 and temp_count >= -999 then
      return FOUR_DIGIT_FONT_SIZE
  else
      return FIVE_DIGIT_FONT_SIZE
  end
end


function GetCounterDetails(GUID)
-- Returns a library with parameters about the counter associated with the passed GUID

  details = {GUID = GUID}

  -- If looking for details about a defaulted Infinite Supply then there is no token and therefore no GUID
  -- This sets the colors to the specified amount from variables at the top of this code for the bank.
  -- Otherwise, if it's not a bank then it returns information about the indicated company counter token.
  if GUID == "Infinite Supply" then
    details.name = "the ".. infinite_supply_name
    details.transaction_button_name = infinite_supply_name
    details.color = bank_background_color
    details.font_color = bank_font_color
  elseif GUID ~= nil then
    counter = getObjectFromGUID(GUID)
    details.name = counter.getVar("counter_controller")
    details.transaction_button_name = counter.getVar("counter_transact_button_name")
    details.color = counter.getColorTint()

    if buttons_created_already == true then
      -- This grabs all button info from the counter associated with the passed GUID
      buttons = counter.getButtons()

      -- This grabs the font color of the value of the counter, and this could be used for setting a transaction button font color if they are used.
      for index, info in ipairs(buttons) do
        if index == 1 then
          details.font_color = info.font_color
        end
      end
    end
  end

  return details
end

  Wait.time(function()
    updateValue()

    end, 0.05)
  end
]]

    if reset_hold == false then
      ChangeTransactButtonColors(object, player_color, 1, false)
    else
      TransactResetTimer()
    end
  end, 20)
end

-- Create buttons based on the button parameters
function createButtons()
    value_button_parameters.label = tostring(count)
    value_button_parameters.font_size = getValueButtonFontSize()

    -- This creates the big value number in the middle of the counter
    self.createButton(value_button_parameters)

    -- This creates the customization options button
    self.createButton(type_button_parameters)

    -- Everything within this If statement relates to having adjustment buttons on the counter.
    -- If this is set to "false" then the counter is only adjustable by outside means (specifically if this is a finite bank for other counters to interact with).
    if any_adjustment_buttons == true then
      -- Everything within this If statement relates to having the player counter transact with company counters.
      -- If this is set to "false" then this counter will not interact with any other counters of the same "type"
      if any_transaction_buttons == true then
        UpdateCounterGUIDs()

        -- This creates the "Transacting with" display button.
        self.createButton(transact_display_parameters)

        button_count = 1
        current_vertical_position = transact_BUTTON_VERTICAL_POSITION + (transact_BUTTON_HEIGHT * 0.00097)

        -- This cycles through every item in the counter_GUIDs table, that has GUIDs of all counters that have the same "type"
        for index, GUID in ipairs(counter_GUIDs) do

          -- This makes sure the number of buttons per row matches the value shown in Customization.
          -- It also makes sure the buttons are evenly spaced out depending on the height specified in Customization.
          if button_count > buttons_per_row then
            current_vertical_position = current_vertical_position + (transact_BUTTON_HEIGHT* 0.0021)
            button_count = 1
          end

          -- This creates a new function for the transaction button to then interact with when changing the transaction target.
          _G['ClickFunction' .. index] = function(object, player_color)
            ChangeTransactButtonColors(object, player_color, index, false)
            TransactResetTimer()
          end

          -- This figures out what the central position is considering the button's width and the number of buttons in the row.
          transact_BUTTONS_START_HORIZONTAL_POSITION = (buttons_per_row - 1) * (transact_BUTTON_WIDTH * 0.00105) * -1

          -- This bundles all the necessary information for the creation of the transaction button
          button_parameters = {
            click_function = 'ClickFunction' .. index,
            function_owner = self,
            label = GetCounterDetails(GUID).transaction_button_name,
            position = {  (transact_BUTTONS_START_HORIZONTAL_POSITION + (button_count - 1)*(transact_BUTTON_WIDTH * 0.0021)),
                           0.1,
                           current_vertical_position},
            width = transact_BUTTON_WIDTH,
            height = transact_BUTTON_HEIGHT,

function OpenCustomization(player, value, id)
-- Function to open the customization XML window

    -- This recreates the list of counters that share a type because new counters might have been made, or had types changed to match.
      UpdateCounterGUIDs()

    -- This changes the XML values to match the current values for all these customization attributes.
    self.UI.setAttribute("NumberOfRows", "text", buttons_per_row)
    self.UI.setAttribute("TransactionButtonWidth","text", transact_BUTTON_WIDTH)
    self.UI.setAttribute("TransactionButtonHeight","text", transact_BUTTON_HEIGHT)
    self.UI.setAttribute("FiftiesToggle", "isOn",fifty_buttons)
    self.UI.setAttribute("CounterType", "text", self.getGMNotes())
    self.UI.setAttribute("CounterName", "text", counter_controller)
    self.UI.setAttribute("CounterTransactButtonName", "text", counter_transact_button_name)
    self.UI.setAttribute("TransactionButtonsToggle", "isOn",any_transaction_buttons)
    self.UI.setAttribute("InfiniteSupplyName", "text", infinite_supply_name)
    self.UI.setAttribute("MoneySymbol", "text", money_symbol)
    self.UI.setAttribute("TransactableToggle", "isOn", transactable)
    self.UI.setAttribute("ShowTypeToggle", "isOn", show_type)
    --self.UI.setAttribute("TransactionsToggle", "isOn", transact_with_others)



    -- This grabs all XML data and puts it into a table.
    local xml = self.UI.getXmlTable()

    -- This builds the dropdown options for which ledger options are used and modifies the XML data table accordingly.
    xml[2].children[8].children[5].children[2].children[1].children = {}

    for _, value in ipairs(ledger_options) do
      if value == ledger_option then
        is_selected = true
      else
        is_selected = false
      end
      add_adjustment_buttons_option = {
          tag="Option",
          value = value,
          attributes={selected = is_selected},
          children={}
      }
      table.insert(xml[2].children[8].children[5].children[2].children[1].children, add_adjustment_buttons_option)
    end

    -- This builds the dropdown options for changing the background color and modifies the XML data table accordingly.
    xml[2].children[8].children[6].children[2].children[1].children = {}
    for _, color in ipairs(color_options) do
      if trunc(self.getColorTint().r,1) == trunc(color.r,1) and trunc(self.getColorTint().g,1) == trunc(color.g,1) and trunc(self.getColorTint().b,1) == trunc(color.b,1) then
        is_selected = true
      else
        is_selected = false
      end
      add_BGcolor_option = {
          tag="Option",
          value = color.color_name,
          attributes={selected = is_selected},
          children={}
      }
      table.insert(xml[2].children[8].children[6].children[2].children[1].children, add_BGcolor_option)
    end

    -- This builds the dropdown options for changing the shown value color and modifies the XML data table accordingly.
    xml[2].children[8].children[7].children[2].children[1].children = {}
    for _, color in ipairs(color_options) do
      if trunc(VALUE_BUTTON_FONT_COLOR[1],1) == trunc(color.r,1) and trunc(VALUE_BUTTON_FONT_COLOR[2],1) == trunc(color.g,1) and trunc(VALUE_BUTTON_FONT_COLOR[3],1) == trunc(color.b,1) then
        is_selected = true
      else
        is_selected = false
      end
      add_value_color_option = {
          tag="Option",
          value = color.color_name,
          attributes={selected = is_selected},
          children={}
      }
      table.insert(xml[2].children[8].children[7].children[2].children[1].children, add_value_color_option)
    end


    -- This builds the dropdown options for which adjustment buttons are shown and modifies the XML data table accordingly.
    xml[2].children[8].children[8].children[2].children[1].children = {}
    if any_adjustment_buttons == false then
      current_shown_adjustment_buttons = "e"
    elseif five_buttons == false then
      current_shown_adjustment_buttons = "1"
    elseif five_buttons == true and fifty_buttons == false then
      current_shown_adjustment_buttons = "5"
    elseif fifty_buttons == true then
      current_shown_adjustment_buttons = "0"
    end

    for _, value in ipairs(adjustment_button_options) do
      if string.sub(value, -1) == current_shown_adjustment_buttons then
        is_selected = true
      else
        is_selected = false
      end
      add_adjustment_buttons_option = {
          tag="Option",
          value = value,
          attributes={selected = is_selected},
          children={}
      }
      table.insert(xml[2].children[8].children[8].children[2].children[1].children, add_adjustment_buttons_option)
    end

    UpdateCounterGUIDs()

    -- This builds the dropdown options for all the counters that can be set to the default transaction target and modifies the XML data table accordingly.
    add_default_option ={ tag="Option",
                  value = "Infinite Supply",
                  attributes={},
                  children={}
    }
    xml[2].children[8].children[10].children[2].children[1].children = {add_default_option}
    log(default_transact_GUID)
    for _, GUID in ipairs(counter_GUIDs) do
      if GUID ~= "Infinite Supply" then
        if default_transact_GUID == GUID then
          is_selected = true
        else
          is_selected = false
        end
        add_default_option = {
            tag="Option",
            value = GetCounterDetails(GUID).transaction_button_name ..": ".. GetCounterDetails(GUID).GUID,
            attributes={selected = is_selected},
            children={}
        }
        table.insert(xml[2].children[8].children[10].children[2].children[1].children, add_default_option)
      end
    end

    -- Replaces this counter's XML data with the modified data from the XML table that was created.
    self.UI.setXmlTable(xml)

    -- This un-hides the Customization XML window so that it's visible and able to be used.
    self.UI.show("Customization_Window")

    -- Changes the "Customization" button's colors to show that it's currently in use.
--    self.editButton({index=1, color=ADJUSTMENT_BUTTON_FONT_COLOR, font_color=ADJUSTMENT_BUTTON_BACKGROUND_COLOR})

    customization_open = true
end


function CloseCustomization(player, value, id)
-- This closes (hides) the Customization XML window.
    UpdateCounterGUIDs()

    self.UI.hide("Customization_Window")

    self.UI.hide("Customization_Explanations")
    customization_explanations = false

    customization_open = false
    UpdateAfterCustomization()

    -- Changes the "Customization" button's colors to show that it's no longer in use.
--    self.editButton({index=1, color=ADJUSTMENT_BUTTON_BACKGROUND_COLOR, font_color=ADJUSTMENT_BUTTON_FONT_COLOR})
end


function ToggleCustomizationExplanations()
-- This opens and closes the "help" panel which explains all the customization options --
  if customization_explanations == true then
    self.UI.hide("Customization_Explanations")
    customization_explanations = false
  else
    self.UI.show("Customization_Explanations")
    customization_explanations = true
  end
end

function TintToText()
  for _, color in ipairs(color_options) do
    if trunc(self.getColorTint().r,1) == trunc(color.r,1) and trunc(self.getColorTint().g,1) == trunc(color.g,1) and trunc(self.getColorTint().b,1) == trunc(color.b,1) then
      bg_color = color.color_name
    end
  end

  return bg_color
end

-- This exists so that the code doesn't have an error. leave it and ignore it.
function NotARealFunction()
end

-- This is a nice little function I found somewhere online that makes truncating a value simple to do.
function trunc(num, digits)
  local mult = 10^(digits)
  return math.modf(num*mult)/mult
end

-- This is an awesome little function I found online that "dumps" all information from a table into the chat box
-- and is entirely used for debugging and discovery. I kept it here because I may need it for future development on this counter.
function dump(o)
   if type(o) == 'table' then
      local s = '{ '
      for k,v in pairs(o) do
         if type(k) ~= 'number' then k = '"'..k..'"' end
         s = s .. '['..k..'] = ' .. dump(v) .. ','
      end
      return s .. '} \n'
   else
      return tostring(o)
   end
end
